title: Branch numbers of Banco Santander globally 2012 to 2019
summary: This is a line chart with an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Number of branches, containing a total of 8 data points.
Overall Number of branches has decreased over the Year.

Number of branches is slightly decreasing from 2012 to 2013, roughly constant from 2013 to 2015, slightly increasing from 2015 to 2017, roughly constant from 2017 to 2018, and finally slightly decreasing from 2018 to 2019.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2016 and 2017.
The highest Number of branches, of value 14392.0 was reached at Year 2012
The lowest Number of branches, of value 11952.0 was reported at Year 2019
